  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:55",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "περιαψάντων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", more strongly than ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἁψάντων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (T.R.) suggests the idea of a well-kindled fire giving a good blaze, supplying light as well as heat. Who kindled it did not need to be said. It was kindled in the open court of the high priest’s house, and was large enough for the attendants to sit around it in the chilly spring night (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "συγκαθισάντων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μέσος αὐτῶν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Peter sat ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "among",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " them. Was that an acted denial, or was he simply seeking warmth, and taking his risk?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
