            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "It was like the impetuosity of his character, but most unwise for one of his temperament. St John says (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") that ‘he stood,’ and perhaps we have here a touch of restlessness.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a certain maid",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Apparently the portress (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 18:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") who had been meanwhile relieved, and who, after a fixed gaze, recognised Peter as the man whom she had admitted. She therefore exclaimed, “This fellow ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "too",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (as well as John) was with Him.” The reports of the Evangelists differ, but each faithfully preserves the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "kai.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a certain maid beheld him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The accounts of these denials by the Evangelists are (as St Augustine says of their narratives generally) “various, but not contrary.” They are capable of perfectly easy and perfectly natural reconcilement, and are a valuable proof of independence.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
